race.comment: SUPREME LADY (5) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by 6 lengths at this track in a handy 18.05 beating Three Hundred. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Looks the testing material. AUSSIE RATTLER (2) has shown good improvement at his last two starts, most recently finishing 2nd at Maitland over 400m. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Well placed and gets his chance. SAY YOUR PRAYERS (1) finished in the placings last start and deserves some thought. Something for the Multiples: PRINCESS MIKA (7)
